Title: Wrath of the Titans Official Trailer #1 - Sam Worthington Movie (2012) HD
Comment: The movie was ultimately disappointing and the ending anticlimactic, but I still loved Sam Worthington, Liam Neeson, and the action. What really hurt it was that it was too formulaic and fast paced, characters just going through the motions. It would have been better if they had played deeper to the Greek lore, had more plot twists, and expanded the battles beyond hitting each other with weapons and CGI magic. What if Hephaestus had turned out to be orchestrating the titans' return all along as revenge for being sapped of his power by the petty Zeus? What if Ares had hesitated about killing Perseus by using some Godly telepathy to read his mind, feeling all the pain he's experienced? What if Io from Clash of the Titans (Gemma Arterton) turned out to be one of many priestesses who watched over Demi-Gods, and their secret order came to help Andromeda's army in the final act? They could have taken Helius to train him at the end while Perseus left to fight the remaining titans. They could even have shown Mount Olympus crumbling as new titans rose up stomping over its ruins with a roar on a cliffhanger. My point is, there are several ways this movie could have been good if they added more intrigue and most importantly, made us care about what was going on. It sucks that we'll probably never see the third planned film Return of the Gods now, but that's Hollywood, I guess...
